p2
VTeenager impresses with Tamil songs
p3
sVnews
p4
VThe teenager, who also is a student of Bharatanatyam, commenced her concert with an impressive varnam in Vanthanadharini ragam set to Rupaka talamKanaka, a class X student of Sankara Matriculation School, Peralam in Tiruvarur district, made her performance lively  by presenting the compositions of eminent Tamil poets including Subramanya Bharati and Bharatidasan. The performance reflected her interest and talent in rendering even songs said to have been composed by Sidhars.The highlight of Kanaka&#8217;s concert was &#8216;Neela malar kola&#8230;&#8217; composed by Oothukkadu Venkatakavi in Vasanta (Adi).  With her mellifluous voice, she kept the audience spell bound through the 40 minutes of her main piece.The song &#8216;Pullai piranthalum&#8230;&#8217; (Ragamalika) composed by Siddhars as well as &#8216;Vantha Vinaiyum&#8230;&#8217; of Kumaragurubarar in Valachi (Adi)  lent a variety to her performance.  Subramania Bharati&#8217;s &#8216;Theeradha vilaiyattu pillai&#8230;&#8217; (ragamalika) and &#8216;Asai mukam maranthathu aeno&#8230;&#8217; brought up the tail with  Kanaka concluding the performance with a song in 19 ragas from the cassette she had released.Sherthalai M.N.Sathiyamoorthy on the violin, Tiruchi B. Swaminathan on the &#8216;mridangam&#8217; and Nellai Krishna on the ghatam provided able assistance.The secretary of Rasika Ranjana Sabha, N. Sekar, was the chief guest.  Commending her achievement in both vocal and Bharathanatyam, the president of the Tiruchi Tamizh Isai Sangam, L.N.Lakshmanan announced that Kanaka would be conferred the title &#8216;Tamizh Isai Thendral&#8217; during the Tamil New Year&#8217;s Day celebrations in April next year.SYED MUTHAHAR SAQAF
